description:
This is a 6 minute workout called 'Instructional: 3 Points of Contact' from the channel Mac Evans.
The workout falls under Warm-up/Warm-up.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Masterclass Workout and The Foundation Builder vibe.
The The Masterclass Workout vibe means Technique-driven, focused, skill-building. This is especially good for Those who love precision and mastery in movement. The The Foundation Builder vibe means Strengthen weak points, rebuild, perfect the basics. This is especially good for Those coming back from injury or refining fundamentals..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Ensure you have a strong foundation in the 3 points of contact for every stroke with Mac....
